The paper focuses on using reinforcement learning to optimize the compilation of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application of this optimization is for deep neural networks used in computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adaptive sampling to improve the efficiency of the optimization process, which could also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
